# Svelte Blog Core Rules

## Project Structure
- src/
  - lib/components/{layout,content,ui}
  - lib/{server,stores,utils}
  - routes/
  - params/
  - app.html, error.html
  - hooks.{client,server}.ts
  - app.d.ts
- static/{images,fonts}
- tests/
- config files (ts/vite/tailwind)

## Naming
- PascalCase: components
- camelCase: variables/functions
- kebab-case: files
- UPPERCASE: constants

## Core Requirements
- TypeScript strict mode
- Svelte 5 runes ($state, $derived, $effect)
- Mobile-first Tailwind design
- WCAG 2.1 Level AA accessibility
- SSR/SSG optimization
- Dark mode support

## Component Guidelines
- .svelte.ts extension
- Explicit props and types
- Snippet syntax with @render
- Error boundaries
- Loading states
- Proper ARIA labels

## Content Features
- Markdown with preview
- Autosave drafts
- Image optimization
- Code syntax highlighting
- Search functionality

## Security
- Input sanitization
- CSRF protection
- Auth handling
- File upload validation

## Performance
- Lazy loading
- Image optimization
- 90+ Lighthouse score
- Dynamic imports
